      • createDataTable

        public static RDataTable createDataTable(RData rData)
                                  throws RDataException
        Create an RDataTable using the data found within the RData instance provided on the call to intialize the table data.

        The following RData concrete types are all accepted on this call:

        • RDataFrame
        • RNumericMatrix
        • RStringMatrix
        • RBooleanMatrix
        • RNumericVector
        • RStringVector
        • RBooleanVector
        • RDateVector

        All other RData types are rejected with an RDataException.

        Throws:
        RDataException

      • createDataTable

        public static RDataTable createDataTable(java.io.InputStream is,
                                         java.lang.String delimiter,
                                         boolean hasHeader)
                                  throws RDataException
        Create an RDataTable using the data found in the file represented by the InputStream parameter.

        Set a value for the delimiter paramter that matches the data delimiter in the file being ingested.

        Enable the hasHeader parameter value if the first line in the file holds header values, as distinct to data values.

        Throws:
        RDataException

      • createDataTable

        public static RDataTable createDataTable(java.io.InputStream is,
                                         java.lang.String delimiter,
                                         boolean hasHeader,
                                         boolean nullMissingData)
                                  throws RDataException
        Create an RDataTable using the data found in the file represented by the InputStream parameter.

        Set a value for the delimiter paramter that matches the data delimiter in the file being ingested.

        Enable the hasHeader parameter value if the first line in the file holds header values, as distinct to data values.

        Enable the nullMissingData parameter value if you want the RDataTable to inject null values into the table data where asymmetrical data is found in the file.

        Throws:
        RDataException
